This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Information Security (cs.NI) as it discusses the use of software-defined networking and network function virtualisation in the context of 5G networks. It also mentions load balancing and carrier aggregation, which are common techniques used in network optimization. The sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY) is also likely as the paper discusses the architecture design principles of the SPEED-5G system. The sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) is possible as the paper mentions the use of dynamic channel selection, which can be used to improve security by avoiding interference from unauthorized sources. The sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT) is possible as the paper discusses the use of KPIs to evaluate the performance of the system. Finally, the sub-category of Architecture (cs.AR) is possible as the paper discusses the design principles of the SPEED-5G architecture.
